FlavorText: "Few things embolden the spirit like a powerful enemy lying dead at your feet." -Andomiel Chu, Master Gem Cutter of Xiansai.

Passive.Text: Gain 20% increased damage for 30.0 seconds after killing an elite pack.
Increases damage against elites by 15.0% (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Bane of the Powerful

FlavorText: Lady Tu de Qing commissioned this gem from the workshops of Xiansai, saying "I prefer my targets asleep or drunk. Barring that, I'll take sluggish."

Passive.Text: Increase damage against enemies under the effects of control-impairing effects by 15.00%.
Gain an aura that reduces the movement speed of enemies within 15 yards by 30%. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Bane of the Trapped

FlavorText: This stone twinkles with low level light, inviting its bearer to dream of higher ambitions.

Passive.Text: Monster kills grant +500 experience.
Level requirement of the item this gem is socketed into is set to 1. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Gem of Ease

FlavorText: The madwoman Arianne believed she could cut a gem that would make for her a hood of lightning. "Lightning," she was heard to mutter "On my head!" Her body was discovered some weeks later, with no hair, clutching this gem.

Passive.Text: 15% chance on hit to gain a Wreath of Lightning, dealing 600.0% weapon damage as Lightning every second to nearby enemies for 3 seconds.
While under the effect of the Wreath of Lightning, gain 25% increased movement speed. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Wreath of Lightning

FlavorText: The poison mixers of Xiansai tell of a sickly gem cutter named Zhong Yi Rou who would come by their vats and scream "I'll put you all out of work someday! Yes I will!"

Passive.Text: Poison all enemies hit for 2000% weapon damage over 10 seconds.
All enemies you poison take 10% increased damage from all sources. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Gem of Efficacious Toxin

FlavorText: Xiangyi, most beautiful of Xiansai master gem cutters, crafted this gem in honor of a former lover. The angrier she got, the faster she worked, and the gem was ready in no time. Only after she had tested its efficacy was she finally satisfied.

Passive.Text: Critical hits cause the enemy to bleed for 1200.0% weapon damage as Physical over 3 seconds.
Gain Blood Frenzy, granting you 3% increased Attack Speed for each bleeding enemy within 20 yards. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Pain Enhancer

FlavorText: “It was said that once a year, the two lovers would arrive at opposite river banks. A bridge of birds would form so they could touch. When they parted, their tears filled the land. Mirinae is one such tear. The sadness and rage in its core will only affect those close to it.” -Scholar Sojin Hwang

Passive.Text: 15% chance on hit to smite a nearby enemy for 2000% weapon damage as Holy.
Smite a nearby enemy every 5 seconds. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Mirinae, Teardrop of the Starweaver

FlavorText: "You do not need to be stronger than your enemy, if you are faster of mind and body." -Queen Seondeok

Passive.Text: 50.0% chance on hit to gain Swiftness, increasing your Attack Speed by 1% for 4 seconds. This effect stacks up to 15 times.
Gain 1% Cooldown Reduction per stack of Swiftness. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Gogok of Swiftness

FlavorText: “Some say this stone derives its power from its owners life force, which is shortened with each use. Well I say any fight I can walk away from is a victory, and tomorrow can take care of itself.” - Famed warrior Lenalas, the day before his death

Passive.Text: While under any control-impairing effects, reduce all damage taken by 30.0%.
Heal for 20% of maximum life when hit by a control-impairing effect. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Invigorating Gemstone

FlavorText: This stone shares its powerful heart with those who serve the bearer.

Passive.Text: Increase the damage of your pets by 15.00%.
Your pets take 25% less damage. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Enforcer

FlavorText: Precious stones can sometimes be found among the peaks of Ivgorod. The harmonics of these gems, while in combat, are said to forestall death itself.

Passive.Text: 25% of all damage taken is instead staggered and dealt to you over 3.00 seconds.
10% chance on kill to clear all staggered damage. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Moratorium

FlavorText: Legend says this gem was crafted by Zei to torment fleeing enemies. Other legends claim that Zei never existed.

Passive.Text: Damage you deal is increased by 4.00% for every 10 yards between you and the enemy hit. Maximum 20.00% increase at 50 yards.
20% chance on hit to Stun the enemy for 1 second. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Zei's Stone of Vengeance

FlavorText: "A simple task performed a thousand times may seem a drudgery, yet the power it creates is immeasurable." - Matriarch Lian Rasmussen

Passive.Text: Increase the damage of primary skills by 25.00%.
Primary skills heal you for 2% of maximum Life on hit. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Simplicity's Strength

FlavorText: "Rumors speak of a greedy Baroness who sends forth minions to collect treasure, equipped with gems to aid in gathering ever more. Boon of the Hoarder is said to be one of these precious gems." -Abd al-Hazir

Passive.Text: 25.0% chance on killing an enemy to cause an explosion of gold.
Gain 30% increased movement speed for 2 seconds after picking up gold. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Boon of the Hoarder

FlavorText: "Given enough resources, one is possessed of an absolute and infinite potentiality." -High Priest Baek

Passive.Text: Gain 0.5% increased damage for 3 seconds after spending primary resource. This effect stacks up to 20 times.
Gain 0.5% increased Armor for every stack. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Taeguk

FlavorText: Chuanyang of Xiansai designed a gem which would transport magical energies from their target to the workshop of his greatest competitor, Chau Thanh. He created several copies of this gem before he mysteriously disappeared.

Passive.Text: Gain 10.0% non-Physical damage reduction.
While below half Life, your resistances to Cold, Fire, Lightning, Poison, and Arcane are increased by 75%. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Esoteric Alteration

FlavorText: The gizzard of the molten wildebeest evinced such extraordinary properties when steeped in the correct mixture of alchemical reagents that the animals were hunted to extinction long ago.

Passive.Text: Regenerates 10000 Life per Second.
After not taking damage for 4 seconds, gain an absorb shield for 200% of your total Life per Second. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Molten Wildebeest's Gizzard

FlavorText: After the defeat of Malthael, Diadra the Scholar wandered the world. She studied the gem cutters of Xiansai, and brought their secrets back to Westmarch. Bane of the Stricken is the first gem to come out of her Westmarch workshop.

Passive.Text: Each attack you make against an enemy increases the damage it takes from your attacks by 4% Weapon damage.
Allied players, followers, and pets also benefit from this effect. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Bane of the Stricken

FlavorText: Chau Thanh of Guozhi designed a gem which would transport the pain and suffering of a physical attack to an undisclosed location. When asked about the ultimate destination of this damage, she would simply smile and mutter “Well deserved. Well deserved.”

Passive.Text: Gain 10.0% melee damage reduction.
While below 30% Life, you may move unhindered through enemies. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Mutilation Guard

FlavorText: “I made a very pretty gemstone once, to use should I ever come to face Dirgest, but I was hungry so I traded it for spiced meats and some wine. Those meats were excellent!”-Covetous Shen

Passive.Text: Your overhealing from Life per Hit and Life per Second are applied as an absorb shield for up to 10% of your maximum Life.
Gain X. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Shen's Delight

FlavorText: Adventurers used to speak fondly of splint mail armor that would freeze their opponents in place. The sickly gem cutter, Zhong Yi Rou heard these tales and set out to create a gem that could do the same."I'll make a few modifications all my own, yes I will," she was heard to mutter.

Passive.Text: Your Cold skills now apply Chill effects and your Chill effects now Slow enemy movement by an additional 5.0%.
Gain 10% increased Critical Hit Chance against Chilled and Frozen enemies. (Requires Rank 25)

Name: Iceblink
